title: 4Sum
description: Given an array nums of n integers, return an array of all the unique quadruplets [nums[a], nums[b], nums[c], nums[d]] such that 0 <= a, b, c, d < n, a, b, c, and d are distinct, and nums[a] + nums[b] + nums[c] + nums[d] == target. Each quadruplet should be sorted in ascending order. The quadruplets should be separated by newlines, and each quadruplet should be space-separated. The list of quadruplets should be sorted lexicographically.
input_format: The first line contains integers separated by space (nums). The second line contains the target integer.
output_format: Unique quadruplets separated by newlines, each quadruplet space-separated and sorted. The list of quadruplets must be sorted.
